pokedexEntries.red: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.
pokedexEntries.blue: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.
pokedexEntries.yellow: Swims powerfully using all the muscles in its body. It can even overtake champion swimmers.
pokedexEntries.gold: This strong and skilled swimmer is even capable of crossing the Pacific Ocean just by kicking.
pokedexEntries.silver: Although an energetic, skilled swimmer that uses all of its muscles, it lives on dry land.
pokedexEntries.crystal: It can use its well-developed arms and legs to run on the surface of the water for a split second.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Poliwrath's highly developed, brawny muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. It is so tirelessly strong, this Pokémon can swim back and forth across the Pacific Ocean without effort.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Poliwrath's highly developed, brawny muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. It is so tirelessly strong, this Pokémon can swim back and forth across the Pacific Ocean without effort.
pokedexEntries.emerald: Its highly developed muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. This Pokémon can swim back and forth across the Pacific Ocean without effort.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: An adept swimmer, it knows the front crawl, butterfly, and more. It is faster than the best human swimmers.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: A swimmer adept at both the front crawl and breaststroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.
pokedexEntries.diamond: With its extremely tough muscles, it can keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.

pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: Poliwrath's highly developed, brawny muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. It is so tirelessly strong, this Pokémon can swim back and forth across the ocean without effort.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: Poliwrath's highly developed, brawny muscles never grow fatigued, however much it exercises. It is so tirelessly strong, this Pokémon can swim back and forth across the ocean without effort.
pokedexEntries.sun: Poliwrath in the Alola region are strong swimmers that use the breaststroke. Many children learn to swim by imitating Poliwrath.
pokedexEntries.moon: Its percentage of body fat is nearly zero. Its body is entirely muscle, which makes it heavy and forces its swimming prowess to develop.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: It’s quite a gifted swimmer, even among Water-type Pokémon, but it normally spends its time on land.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: The muscles it has developed through swimming are thick and powerful. When it lands a square punch, it can turn huge boulders to dust.
